snippet.textDisplay: Today, I returned to hostel from home. This soul-soother of a song found me minutes into my ride to the airport, and I've lost count of the number of times I've listened to it since. And every single time, I break into sobs. This is my first time living away from my parents, and every day apart from them feels like a pale imitation of life. This song is like warm honeyed milk on a sleepless night for the heart. It has begun to heal something in me. I cannot describe how grateful I am that this song exists, and that I found it exactly when I needed it the most.

snippet.textDisplay:
Shreya's voice radiates warmth and peace, creating a tranquil space where you can let go of all your worries. 

The song beautifully captures that feeling of being cradled in your mother’s embrace, where everything else fades away. 

It's a gentle reminder to pause, stop overthinking, and find calm amid life’s constant rush. Shreya’s soulful rendition makes Re Mann not just a song, but a heartfelt experience of peace and reflection.

Love you Shreya... and THANK YOU!❤
